{
  "texts": [
    "For a pre-trained weight matrix W 0 ∈ R d 1 ×d 2 and arbitrary input x, they modify the forward pass as follows 1:",
    "1 In this paper, we use the post-multiplication for simplicity. where",
    "Typically, A is initialized as a Gaussian matrix and B as a zero matrix, so that ∆W is zero at the beginning.",
    "During training, the original weight W 0 is frozen, while A and B contain trainable parameters.",
    "After that, the A and B can be merged into W 0 during inference, thus not introducing any latency."
  ]
}